    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>UNILEVER SHARES FALL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Shares in consumer and food giant Unilever PLC fall 9 percent following its revision downward of sales-growth forecasts (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Shares in the food and consumer giant Unilever P.L.C. fell 9 percent after the British-Dutch company lowered its forecast for annual sales growth from 3 to 4 percent to 2 to 3 percent. The outlook excluded recent acquisitions in the United States like Bestfoods and Ben &amp; Jerry's. In London, Unilever shares fell 41 pence, to 413 pence, or about $6.20.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
      </block>
